{"lemma":"تَقِيٌّ","slug":"تَقِيٌّ","root":"ت.ق.#","root_slug":"ت-ق-_","root_link":"/words/roots/ت-ق-_","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"تَقِيّ","root":"وقي","pos":"N","occurrence_count":4},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["adj","name","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n3989","n3991","n3993"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AA%D9%8E%D9%82%D9%90%D9%8A%D9%8C%D9%91"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"God-fearing, pious, righteous, godly"},{"pos":"name","gloss":"a male given name, Taqi"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n3989","headword_ar":"تَقَى","root":"Quasi tqY: or, accord. to some, tqw","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, K, in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wqY","text_ar":"وقى"},{"kind":"text","text":") and"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, TA,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taqiYa","text_ar":"تَقِىَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, [but the correctness of this I greatly doubt, unless, as appears to be the case, it is meant to be understood as an intrans. verb,]) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taqoYN","text_ar":"تَقْىٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S and TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tqY","text_ar":"تقى"},{"kind":"text","text":", [which art. I find in only one copy of the S,]) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tuqFY","text_ar":"تُقًى"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tuqaApN","text_ar":"تُقَاةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, and also mentioned in the TA,) of which"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tuqFY","text_ar":"تُقًى"},{"kind":"text","text":"is pl., or coll. n., (Kzz, IB, Msb,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taqiy~apN","text_ar":"تَقِيَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tiqaA='N","text_ar":"تِقَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Lh, K;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aitaq~aY","text_ar":"اِتَقَّى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, S, Msb, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ait~iqaA='N","text_ar":"اِتِّقَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb) and [quasi-inf. n.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taqiy~apN","text_ar":"تَقِيَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tuqaApN","text_ar":"تُقَاةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wqY","text_ar":"وقى"},{"kind":"text","text":";)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He feared"},{"kind":"text","text":"God: (S and TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tqY","text_ar":"تقى"},{"kind":"text","text":": all else that follows is from art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wqY","text_ar":"وقى"},{"kind":"text","text":"except where reference is made to another art.:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he was cautious of"},{"kind":"text","text":"a thing;"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"guarded,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was on his guard, against"},{"kind":"text","text":"it;"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"prepared, prepared himself,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was in a state of preparation, against"},{"kind":"text","text":"it; or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"feared"},{"kind":"text","text":"it: (K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he looked forward to"},{"kind":"text","text":"a thing,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and guarded against"},{"kind":"text","text":"it,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sought to avoid"},{"kind":"text","text":"it, or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was cautious of"},{"kind":"text","text":"it. (T, TA.) [For other explanations of the latter verb, which apply also to the former, see art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wqY","text_ar":"وقى"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ait~aqaY","text_ar":"اِتَّقَى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AiwotaqaY","text_ar":"اِوْتَقَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (T, S;) then"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AiytaqaY","text_ar":"اِيتَقَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"; then"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ait~aqaY","text_ar":"اِتَّقَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and when this came to be much in use, they imagined the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"t","text_ar":"ت"},{"kind":"text","text":"to be a radical part of the word, and made the word"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AitaqaY","text_ar":"اِتَقَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yataqiY","text_ar":"يَتَقِى"},{"kind":"text","text":", with fet-h to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"t","text_ar":"ت"},{"kind":"text","text":"in each case, and without teshdeed; and not finding any analogue to it in their language, they said"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taqaY","text_ar":"تَقَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yatoqiY","text_ar":"يَتْقِى"},{"kind":"text","text":", like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaDaY","text_ar":"قَضَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaqoDiY","text_ar":"يَقْضِى"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) or, as is said in the T, they suppressed the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"t","text_ar":"ت"},{"kind":"text","text":", and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ait~aqaY","text_ar":"اِتَّقَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"changed into"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"t","text_ar":"ت"},{"kind":"text","text":", in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ait~aqaY","text_ar":"اِتَّقَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", and said"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taqaY","text_ar":"تَقَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yatoqiY","text_ar":"يَتْقِى"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) A poet says, (namely, Khufáf Ibn-Nudbeh, TA,)"},{"kind":"quote","text":"jalaAhaA AlS~ayoqaluwna faA^axolaSuwhaA\n                      \n                     \n                        xifaAfFA kul~uhaA yatoqiY biA^avori"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, as some read it,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yataqiY","text_ar":"يَتَقِى"},{"kind":"text","text":", with the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"t","text_ar":"ت"},{"kind":"text","text":"movent, but without teshdeed; (S;) and this latter, accord."},{"kind":"page_break","n":310},{"kind":"text","text":"to IB, is the right reading. (TA.) [See this verse explained in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Avr","text_ar":"اثر"},{"kind":"text","text":".] IB adds that Aboo-Sa'eed [app. meaning As] disallowed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taqaY","text_ar":"تَقَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yatoqiY","text_ar":"يَتْقِى"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taqoYN","text_ar":"تَقْىٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; saying that it would require the imperative to be"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aitoqi","text_ar":"اِتْقِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is not said; and this, he states, is right: [for] J says that the imperative used is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taqi","text_ar":"تَقِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Fear thou,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beware thou,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.], as in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taqi A@ll~`hi","text_ar":"تَقِ ا@للّٰهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Fear thou God"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; and to a woman,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taqiY","text_ar":"تَقِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"; formed from the verb"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AitaqaY","text_ar":"اِتَقَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", without tesh-deed, by the suppression of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A","text_ar":"ا"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["T","TA","K","Kzz","IB","Msb","S"]},{"entry_id":"n3991","headword_ar":"تُقًى","root":"Quasi tqY: or, accord. to some, tqw","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taqowaY","text_ar":"تَقْوَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n3993","headword_ar":"تَقِىٌّ","root":"Quasi tqY: or, accord. to some, tqw","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", applied to a man, (Msb, K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waqiY~N","text_ar":"وَقِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mut~aqK","text_ar":"مُتَّقٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Fearing; cautious;"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.: (see 1:) and particularly"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having a reverential,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pious, fear of God:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or simply"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pious:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one who preserves,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"guards, himself,"},{"kind":"text","text":"accord. to some,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"exceedingly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"extraordinarily, from sin, either of commission or of omission:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(see 8 in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wqY","text_ar":"وقى"},{"kind":"text","text":":)] accord. to IDrd, one"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who preserves,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"guards, himself from punishment"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the world to come"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and from acts of disobedience, by righteous conduct:"},{"kind":"text","text":"from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waqayotu nafosiY","text_ar":"وَقَيْتُ نَفْسِى"},{"kind":"text","text":": said by the grammarians to be originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waquwYN","text_ar":"وَقُوىٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; then,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taquwYN","text_ar":"تَقُوىٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": or, accord. to Aboo-Bekr, [originally] of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEiylN","text_ar":"فَعِيلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as is indicated by the first of its pls. mentioned below: but he who says that it is [originally] of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEuwlN","text_ar":"فَعُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"says that it has that pl. because it has become like a word [originally] of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEiylN","text_ar":"فَعِيلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"righteous, virtuous, just,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"honest;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tqY","text_ar":"تقى"},{"kind":"text","text":";)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faAjirN","text_ar":"فَاجِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (idem in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"br","text_ar":"بر"},{"kind":"text","text":":) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^atoqiyaA='u","text_ar":"اَتْقِيَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tqY","text_ar":"تقى"},{"kind":"text","text":", and K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tuqawaA='u","text_ar":"تُقَوَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) which is extr., and of a class disallowed by Sb, (TA,) [and app. also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tuqaApN","text_ar":"تُقَاةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v. suprà.]"}],"source_refs":["Msb","K","TA","S"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}